        <h1>
            NYU Undergraduate Internships: Overview
        </h1>

        <ul>

            <li>
                Please contact the Office of Global Services for details on F-1
                internship eligibility.
            </li>

            <li>
                Minimum GPA 2.50.
            </li>

            <li>
                No outstanding incompletes!
            </li>

            <li>
                No Fail grades on previous internships.
            </li>

            <li>
                Spring and fall: minimum 12 weeks.
            </li>

            <li>
                Summer: minimum 8 weeks.
            </li>

            <li>
                Minimum hours: 240.
            </li>

            <li>
                Start and end dates must fit within a semester.
            </li>

            <li>
                Full-time students can't work more than 20 hours
                per week while classes are in session.
            </li>

            <li>
                Student must have an appointed supervisor.
            </li>

            <li>
                Students must have an official offer letter.
            </li>

    <li>
        Students must update their placement information through their NYU
        CareerNet Account Profile.
    </li>

    <li>
        Prospective employers must send the advisor a detailed job description.
    </li>

    <li>
        Students will submit their offer letter, job description,
        and printed NYU CareerNet Profile to their departmental adviser.
    </li>

    <li>
        For approved International Students, the faculty adviser will provide
        the Office of Global Scholars (OGS) with all relevant information.
    </li>

    <li>
        The company supervisor must provide a mid-term evaluation and a final
        evaluation to the faculty supervisor.
    </li>
    
    <li>
    The student will submit a project
        report at the end of the term.
    </li>
    
    <li>
        All CP courses will be graded as Pass (P) or Fail (F).
    </li>

    <li>
        Consecutive work experiences may
        be completed with the same employer.
    </li>

        </ul>
